## D. Content Reuse Plan from This Research Package

Each research file feeds specific website pages. This is the production map:

| Research file | Feeds page(s) |
|---|---|
| 00 Overview | Home hero copy, About summary block |
| 01 History and Founders | About → "Our Story", first half of `/method` |
| 02 Philosophy and Mindfulness | About → "Why we teach this", `/for-professionals` opening |
| 03 The Eight-Step Method | `/method/eight-steps` (verbatim source), eight individual cluster pages |
| 04 Tangles Dictionary | `/tangles` library — one page per entry |
| 05 Tools and Materials | `/shop` editorial copy, FAQ entries |
| 06 ZIA Zentangle Inspired Art | `/method/zentangle-vs-zia`, Gallery intro |
| 07 CZT Certification Path | `/czt-directory` intro, "Become a CZT" blog post |
| 08 Global Community and Events | Blog seed posts, Workshops landing intro |
| 09 Therapeutic and Educational Applications | `/for-professionals` (the entire pillar) |
| 10 Taiwan and Chinese-Speaking Market | About → local context, `/czt-directory` Taiwan section |
| 11 Website Architecture Recommendation | This document — internal only |

Production rule: research files are the source of truth. When site copy and a research file disagree, the research file wins until edited.

